Usage: report_sequential [-help] [<topCell|vCell>+] [-deleted] [-full]
                         [-hinst <hInst>] [-mapped] [-optimized]
                         [-out_file <string>]

-help                # Prints out the command usage
<topCell|vCell>+     # Hinsts that are derived from (instantiate) this module
                     # or design. ((topCell|vCell)+, optional)
-deleted             # Generates a report with the deleted flops and the
                     # reason. (bool, optional)
-full                # Generates a report with the sequential name, whether it
                     # was inferred or instantiated, the type of sequential,
                     # and the type of reset.
                     # NOTE:  in the current Genus implementation, this is
                     # -hier. (bool, optional)
-hinst <hInst>       # Hinst for the report.  By default, the design is
                     # reported. ((hInst), optional)
-mapped              # Generates a report with synthesis requirements modified
                     # to map the sequential. (bool, optional)
-optimized           # Generates a report with sequentials optimized to
                     # constants or are unloaded, but have not been removed.
                     # (bool, optional)
-out_file <string>   # File to dump the report.  Default is stdout.
                     # (string, optional)